{"title_page": "Dalray", "text_new": "{{short description|20th-century New Zealand racehorse}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use New Zealand English|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox thoroughbred racehorse\n|horsename= Dalray\n|image= [[File:Dalray 1952 VRC Melbourne Cup Jockey Bill Williamson Trainer Clarrie McCarthy.jpg|260px]]\n|caption= Dalray and [[Bill Williamson]]\n|sire= Balloch (GB)\n|grandsire= Obliterate (GB)\n|dam= Broiveine (NZ)\n|damsire= Broiefort (FR)\n|sex= [[Stallion (horse)|Stallion]]\n|foaled= 1948\n|country= [[New Zealand]]\n|colour= [[Bay (horse)|Bay]]\n|breeder= \n|owner=  Cyril Neville\n|trainer= Clarrie McCarthy\n|record= 27:14\u20132\u20133\n|earnings= \n|race= {{plainlist|\n*[[New Zealand Derby]] (1951)\n*[[Great Northern Derby (race)|Great Northern Derby]] (1952)\n*[[Trentham Stakes]] (1952)\n*[[New Zealand St. Leger]] (1952)\n*[[Colin Stephen Quality Handicap|Colin Stephen Stakes]] (1952)\n*AJC Autumn Stakes (1952)\n*[[AJC Metropolitan Handicap|Metropolitan Handicap]] (1952)\n*[[LKS Mackinnon Stakes]] (1952)\n*[[Melbourne Cup]] (1952)\n*[[VRC Queens Plate]] (1953)}}\n|awards= \n|honours= [[Australian Racing Hall of Fame]]\n|updated= 28 December 2012\n}}\n\n'''Dalray''' was a notable [[New Zealand]] [[thoroughbred]] [[horse|racehorse]] who won the 1952 [[Melbourne Cup]] and [[LKS Mackinnon Stakes|Mackinnon Stakes]].\n\nDalray was also famously a \u2018certainty\u2019 beaten in the 1952 [[Sydney Cup]]. When his owner was quizzed about the defeat he declared \"[[Phar Lap]] got beaten and [[Donald Bradman|Bradman]] got a duck\".<ref>Taylor, M. (2002). ''Century of champions : 100 great Australian and New Zealand horses ''. HarperCollinsPublishers (New Zealand) Limited {{ISBN|1-86950-427-5}}, p. 59</ref>\n\nDalray's career was cut short by injury when he was a four-year-old and he was retired to stud. Amongst his better progeny were Tails (1969 and 1970 [[AJC Metropolitan Handicap|Metropolitan Handicap]]) and Grand Garry (1960 [[Sydney Cup]]).\n\nDalray died from a twisted bowel, aged 23.\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Thoroughbred racing in New Zealand]]\n\n==Citations==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book | last= Taylor | first= Mark | title= Century of champions : 100 great Australian and New Zealand horses | publisher= HarperCollinsPublishers (New Zealand) Limited | isbn = 1-86950-427-5 | year= 2002 | pages= 216 | location=[[New Zealand]]}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dalray}}\n[[Category:Melbourne Cup winners]]\n[[Category:1948 racehorse births]]\n[[Category:Thoroughbred family C3]]\n[[Category:Racehorses bred in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Racehorses trained in New Zealand]]\n\n{{racehorse-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|20th-century New Zealand racehorse}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use New Zealand English|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox thoroughbred racehorse\n|horsename= Dalray\n|image= [[File:Dalray 1952 VRC Melbourne Cup Jockey Bill Williamson Trainer Clarrie McCarthy.jpg|260px]]\n|caption= Dalray and Bill Williamson\n|sire= Balloch (GB)\n|grandsire= Obliterate (GB)\n|dam= Broiveine (NZ)\n|damsire= Broiefort (FR)\n|sex= [[Stallion (horse)|Stallion]]\n|foaled= 1948\n|country= [[New Zealand]]\n|colour= [[Bay (horse)|Bay]]\n|breeder= \n|owner=  Cyril Neville\n|trainer= Clarrie McCarthy\n|record= 27:14\u20132\u20133\n|earnings= \n|race= {{plainlist|\n*[[New Zealand Derby]] (1951)\n*[[Great Northern Derby (race)|Great Northern Derby]] (1952)\n*[[Trentham Stakes]] (1952)\n*[[New Zealand St. Leger]] (1952)\n*[[Colin Stephen Quality Handicap|Colin Stephen Stakes]] (1952)\n*AJC Autumn Stakes (1952)\n*[[AJC Metropolitan Handicap|Metropolitan Handicap]] (1952)\n*[[LKS Mackinnon Stakes]] (1952)\n*[[Melbourne Cup]] (1952)\n*[[VRC Queens Plate]] (1953)}}\n|awards= \n|honours= [[Australian Racing Hall of Fame]]\n|updated= 28 December 2012\n}}\n\n'''Dalray''' was a notable [[New Zealand]] [[thoroughbred]] [[horse|racehorse]] who won the 1952 [[Melbourne Cup]] and [[LKS Mackinnon Stakes|Mackinnon Stakes]].\n\nDalray was also famously a \u2018certainty\u2019 beaten in the 1952 [[Sydney Cup]]. When his owner was quizzed about the defeat he declared \"[[Phar Lap]] got beaten and [[Donald Bradman|Bradman]] got a duck\".<ref>Taylor, M. (2002). ''Century of champions : 100 great Australian and New Zealand horses ''. HarperCollinsPublishers (New Zealand) Limited {{ISBN|1-86950-427-5}}, p. 59</ref>\n\nDalray's career was cut short by injury when he was a four-year-old and he was retired to stud. Amongst his better progeny were Tails (1969 and 1970 [[AJC Metropolitan Handicap|Metropolitan Handicap]]) and Grand Garry (1960 [[Sydney Cup]]).\n\nDalray died from a twisted bowel, aged 23.\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Thoroughbred racing in New Zealand]]\n\n==Citations==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book | last= Taylor | first= Mark | title= Century of champions : 100 great Australian and New Zealand horses | publisher= HarperCollinsPublishers (New Zealand) Limited | isbn = 1-86950-427-5 | year= 2002 | pages= 216 | location=[[New Zealand]]}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dalray}}\n[[Category:Melbourne Cup winners]]\n[[Category:1948 racehorse births]]\n[[Category:Thoroughbred family C3]]\n[[Category:Racehorses bred in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Racehorses trained in New Zealand]]\n\n{{racehorse-stub}}\n", "name_user": "LESHAIGH", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dalray"}
